have: used with the past participle of other verbs to form the present perfect and past perfect:
get: to obtain, buy, or earn something:
zoo: an area in which animals, especially wild animals, are kept so that people can go and look at them or study them
last: (the person or thing) after everyone or everything else:

seem: to give the effect of being; to be judged to be:
take: to remove something, especially without permission:

look: to direct your eyes in order to see:
fight: to use physical force to try to defeat another person or group of people:

Drive: to move or travel on land in a motor vehicle, especially as the person controlling the vehicle's movement:

ask: to put a question to someone, or to request an answer from someone:
